on\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The 37-year-old Scot, who won gold in London 2012 and Rio 2016, is the only player to win back-to-back Olympic titles in singles.\", \"from\": 702, \"to\": 831, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 740, \"end\": 751, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tennis_at_the_2012_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999999976539584, \"rank\": 2.346177612365151e-09, \"text\": \"London 2012\", \"types\": [\"Q500834\", \"Q1656682\", \"Q13219666\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tennis_at_the_2012_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tennis_at_the_2012_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He will be joined by debutants Jack Draper, Cameron Norrie and Dan Evans in what will be his fifth, and possibly final Games.\", \"from\": 832, \"to\": 957, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 863, \"end\": 874, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jack_Draper_(tennis)\", \"score\": 0.9926967693033829, \"rank\": 0.007352941176469691, \"text\": \"Jack Draper\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jack_Draper_(tennis)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jack_Draper_(tennis)\"}, {\"begin\": 876, \"end\": 890, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cameron_Norrie\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Cameron Norrie\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cameron_Norrie\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cameron_Norrie\"}, {\"begin\": 895, \"end\": 904, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Die_Warzau\", \"score\": 0.9729861169141663, \"rank\": 0.0277638936631715, \"text\": \"Dan Evans\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q215380\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Die_Warzau\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Die_Warzau\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It was a landmark day for Draper, the incoming British men\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s singles No.\", \"from\": 959, \"to\": 1033, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1006, \"end\": 1013, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Boxing_Board_of_Control\", \"score\": 0.9996601408552281, \"rank\": 0.00033925686881249506, \"text\": \"British\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Boxing_Board_of_Control\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Boxing_Board_of_Control\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"1, as just hours later the 22-year-old won his maiden ATP Tour title, beating former Wimbledon runner-up Matteo Berrettini 3-6, 7-6 (7-5), 6-4 in the final of the Stuttgart Open.\", \"from\": 1034, \"to\": 1212, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1139, \"end\": 1156, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matteo_Berrettini\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Matteo Berrettini\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matteo_Berrettini\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matteo_Berrettini\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He said after the win: \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cI think (it is) just a lot of hard work.A lot of tough moments the last year or so.\", \"from\": 1214, \"to\": 1323, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s been up and down, but I\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099m really, really glad with the way I played and I think it\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s a testament to the work I\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099ve been doing.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d  Former US Open champion Emma Raducanu was not included in the line-up.\", \"from\": 1324, \"to\": 1537, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1474, \"end\": 1481, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/US_Open_(tennis)\", \"score\": 0.935861658826044, \"rank\": 0.027464247762228403, \"text\": \"US Open\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/US_Open_(tennis)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/US_Open_(tennis)\"}, {\"begin\": 1491, \"end\": 1504, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emma_Raducanu\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Emma Raducanu\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emma_Raducanu\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emma_Raducanu\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The BBC reported that Raducanu, who is still coming back from surgery on her wrists and ankle in 2023 and was ranked too low to qualify automatically for the team, had turned down the offer of a wild card.\", \"from\": 1538, \"to\": 1743, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1542, \"end\": 1545, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC_Sport\", \"score\": 0.9907646991587585, \"rank\": 0.009315149034386629, \"text\": \"BBC\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC_Sport\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC_Sport\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Said the head of Britain\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s Olympic tennis team Iain Bates: \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cI have had various conversations with Emma over the last couple of weeks and a slightly longer period where it\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s very clear how much being part of a British team at an Olympics would mean to her.\", \"from\": 1745, \"to\": 2006, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1847, \"end\": 1851, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tenille_Dashwood\", \"score\": 0.989707625104363, \"rank\": 0.010399215498436549, \"text\": \"Emma\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13474373\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tenille_Dashwood\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tenille_Dashwood\"}, {\"begin\": 1960, \"end\": 1967, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Boxing_Board_of_Control\", \"score\": 0.9996601408552281, \"rank\": 0.00033925686881249506, \"text\": \"British\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Boxing_Board_of_Control\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Boxing_Board_of_Control\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cI think she feels this isn\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t going to be the right timing for her for this summer.\", \"from\": 2008, \"to\": 2095, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s hopefully got many Olympics ahead of her.\", \"from\": 2096, \"to\": 2145, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099m very comfortable with the decision that she\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s made.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d  Current British women\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s singles No.\", \"from\": 2146, \"to\": 2247, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"1 Katie Boulter will make her Olympic debut in the women\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s singles.\", \"from\": 2248, \"to\": 2317, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2250, \"end\": 2263, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katie_Boulter\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Katie Boulter\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katie_Boulter\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katie_Boulter\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Tokyo Games Olympians Neal Skupski and Joe Salisbury will compete in men\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s doubles.\", \"from\": 2318, \"to\": 2403, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2340, \"end\": 2352, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Neal_Skupski\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Neal Skupski\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Neal_Skupski\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Neal_Skupski\"}, {\"begin\": 2357, \"end\": 2360, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Joe_DiMaggio\", \"score\": 0.9999036117778257, \"rank\": 8.813024441541741e-05, \"text\": \"Joe\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Joe_DiMaggio\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Joe_DiMaggio\"}, {\"begin\": 2361, \"end\": 2370, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Salisbury\", \"score\": 0.960637238348744, \"rank\": 0.0409739212886131, \"text\": \"Salisbury\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Salisbury\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Salisbury\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Boulter beat Raducanu 6-7 (13-15), 6-3, 6-4 in the semi-finals of the Nottingham Open on June 16.\", \"from\": 2405, \"to\": 2502, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The match was halted after the first set on June 15 due to bad lighting.\", \"from\": 2503, \"to\": 2575, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Boulter will face Karolina Pliskova in the final.\", \"from\": 2576, \"to\": 2625, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2594, \"end\": 2611, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Karol\\u00edna_Pl\\u00ed\\u0161kov\\u00e1\", \"score\": 0.9999999991223376, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Karolina Pliskova\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Karol\\u00edna_Pl\\u00ed\\u0161kov\\u00e1\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Karol\\u00edna_Pl\\u00ed\\u0161kov\\u00e1\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cThe calibre of the team gets stronger with every Games, and it is great to see a mix of returning and first-time Olympians,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d Team GB chef de mission Mark England said in a statement on June 16.  \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cAndy Murray was our flag bearer in Rio, and he continues to lead by example through his commitment to the Olympic Games and Team GB in what will be his fifth Olympics.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d  The Olympic tennis tournament will run from July 27 to Aug 4 at Roland Garros in Paris.\", \"from\": 2627, \"to\": 3089, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2757, \"end\": 2764, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"score\": 0.9999995456838529, \"rank\": 4.5430533561103105e-07, \"text\": \"Team GB\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\"}, {\"begin\": 2781, \"end\": 2793, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mark_England\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Mark England\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mark_England\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mark_England\"}, {\"begin\": 2830, \"end\": 2841, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Murray\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.9176865256967935e-77, \"text\": \"Andy Murray\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Murray\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Murray\"}, {\"begin\": 2865, \"end\": 2868, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999998356233981, \"rank\": 1.6437669847820368e-07, \"text\": \"Rio\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 2954, \"end\": 2961, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"score\": 0.9999995456838529, \"rank\": 4.5430533561103105e-07, \"text\": \"Team GB\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\"}, {\"begin\": 3083, \"end\": 3088, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999499778, \"rank\": 5.017496293673095e-11, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Meanwhile, Australian top seed Alex de Minaur beat American Sebastian Korda 6-2, 6-4 to win the \\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s-Hertogenbosch grass-court Wimbledon warm-up on June 16\\u00c2\\u00a0in the Netherlands.\", \"from\": 3091, \"to\": 3267, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3102, \"end\": 3112, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"score\": 0.9950135640547936, \"rank\": 0.0031225693048562934, \"text\": \"Australian\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\"}, {\"begin\": 3122, \"end\": 3136, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alex_de_Minaur\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Alex de Minaur\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alex_de_Minaur\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alex_de_Minaur\"}, {\"begin\": 3142, \"end\": 3150, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9955390617243138, \"rank\": 0.0044791889670431975, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 3255, \"end\": 3266, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9858946918839824, \"rank\": 0.0129169469108251, \"text\": \"Netherlands\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The straight-set win ensured the 25-year-old will reach a career-high world ranking of seventh.\", \"from\": 3269, \"to\": 3364, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It was de Minaur\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s second title of the season after winning in Acapulco, Mexico in March, and the ninth of his career.REUTERS, AFP  Olympics 2024  Andy Murray  Emma Raducanu  Olympics  Men's tennis  E-paper  Newsletters  Podcasts  RSS Feed  About Us  Terms & Conditions  Personal Data Protection Notice  Need help?\", \"from\": 3366, \"to\": 3682, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3431, \"end\": 3447, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Acapulco\", \"score\": 0.9999999999536158, \"rank\": 4.653176062925118e-11, \"text\": \"Acapulco, Mexico\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Acapulco